---
---

<section class="py-24 md:py-36 bg-warm-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16">

      <!-- Left column: Year as dramatic typographic element -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-4 reveal">
        <p class="text-storehouse-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase">
          Chapter One
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 font-display text-7xl sm:text-8xl lg:text-9xl text-storehouse-200 leading-none select-none">
          1998
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right column: Prose -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-8">
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-text-deep leading-[1.05] reveal">
          First-time homebuyer.
        </h2>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed max-w-2xl reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <p>
            I was 28 years old and single, working as a database engineer.
            The economy was booming, and I was ready to buy my first house.
          </p>
          <p>
            The bank ran the numbers and pre-approved me for
            <span class="font-semibold text-text-deep">$250,000</span>.
            That was a lot of money back then.
          </p>
          <p>
            Everyone around me was buying as much house as they could afford.
            That's what you did, right? Maximize your investment. Get the
            most house for your money.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Transition line -->
        <div class="mt-12 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="w-12 h-px bg-text-faint/40"></div>
            <p class="font-display text-xl sm:text-2xl text-text-deep">
              I found a real estate agent named Bob.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>
